Key Match Events: The Cleveland Guardians produced an astonishing late comeback to beat the New York Yankees.
Outfielder Jhonkensy Noel forced an extra-inning after a sensational game-tying home run.
Utility player David Fry hit a walk-off homer to secure the victory for Cleveland.
The game went into extra innings, with the Guardians winning 7-5.
Cleveland took a 3-1 lead before back-to-back home runs by Aaron Judge and Giancarlo Stanton gave the Yankees a 4-3 lead.
Jhonkensy Noel tied the game with a two-run home run in the ninth inning.
David Fry hit a 399-foot home run in the bottom of the tenth inning to win the game.
Post-Match Reflections: Travis Kelce expressed his delight on social media, praising the Cleveland Guardians for their remarkable victory.
Kelce, who was born near Cleveland, was ecstatic about the team's performance.
